definitions.definition: The target set into which a function is formally defined to map elements of its domain ; the set denoted Y in the notation f : X → Y .

labels: of a binary relation R between A
subdefinitions.label_groups: more generally , of a binary relation R between A and B

main_definition: ( mathematics , mathematical analysis ) The target set into which a function is formally defined to map elements of its domain ; the set denoted Y in the notation f : X → Y .
